  "text": "where the decision variables are (q, τ ). We will adopt the above notation as a convenient alternative to explicitly stating a lexicographic least-squares problem in the form (2) (a similar approach is taken in [CITATION_1] ). Solving (4) implies finding a pair (q, τ ) that satisfies the dynamics of the system, and x b damps the base velocity as much as possible (in a leastsquares sense). The terminal objective is optional and ensures obtaining a solution such that the Euclidean norm of the joint accelerations is minimized (the use of other terminal objectives could be envisioned). Note that d b is assumed to be unmodeled dynamics.",
